mql is a cloud-native tool for querying your entire infrastructure.

Usage:
  mql [command]

Available Commands:
  completion    Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
  help          Help about any command
  login         Register with Mondoo Platform
  logout        Log out from Mondoo Platform
  providers     Providers add connectivity to all assets
  run           Run an MQL query
  shell         Interactive query shell for MQL
  status        Verify access to Mondoo Platform
  vault         Manage vault environments
  version       Display the mql version

Flags:
      --api-proxy string   Set proxy for communications with Mondoo Platform API
      --auto-update        Enable automatic provider installation and update (default true)
      --config string      Set config file path (default $HOME/.config/mondoo/mondoo.yml)
  -h, --help               help for mql
      --log-level string   Set log level: error, warn, info, debug, trace (default "info")
  -v, --verbose            Enable verbose output

Use "mql [command] --help" for more information about a command.
